<p class=""><h2>Key Challenges in the Milk Aflatoxin Rapid Detection Kits Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> The milk industry faces stringent regulations regarding aflatoxin levels. Compliance with various standards can be complex and costly for manufacturers of detection kits.</li>    <li><strong>Test Accuracy:</strong> While rapid detection kits are crucial for quick results, maintaining a high level of accuracy and reliability can be challenging. False positives or negatives can lead to serious repercussions for producers.</li>    <li><strong>Market Awareness:</strong> Many small-scale dairy producers may lack awareness of the importance of aflatoxin testing. Limited knowledge about the health risks and economic implications can hinder market growth.</li>    <li><strong>Cost Constraints:</strong> The initial cost of implementing robust testing systems can be a barrier, especially for smaller producers with limited budgets. Budget constraints can limit the widespread adoption of the technology.</li>    <li><strong>Technological Advancements:</strong> While there are ongoing innovations in detection methods, keeping pace with these advancements can be difficult for existing manufacturers. They must continually update their products to stay competitive.</li></ul><h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Milk Aflatoxin Rapid Detection Kits Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Increased Consumer Awareness:</strong> Growing consumer awareness regarding food safety and health risks associated with aflatoxin contamination presents a significant opportunity. As consumers demand safer products, the need for effective testing kits increases.</li>    <li><strong>Technological Innovations:</strong> Advances in technology, such as the development of more sensitive assays and user-friendly devices, could spur market growth. Innovations that reduce testing time and improve accuracy are highly sought after.</li>    <li><strong>Global Market Expansion:</stro